---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Section from "../../components/Section.astro";
import Card from "../../components/Card.astro";

---

<BaseLayout>
  <Section>
    <div class="flex flex-col items-center mt-6 mb-12">
      <p class="px-14 py-6 text-center text-4xl font-bold">About me - And how you can help</p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:items-start">
      <div class="space-y-6 text-left">
        <div>
          <p class="px-2 py-3 text-left text-2xl font-bold">About me - The Website Writer</p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-base leading-8 text-[#032922] dark:text-[#f5e5d5]">
          <p>
            At times I am close to a student of everything, and I shall post accordingly. My University degree (in progress) is in Environmental Science and concurrently I am taking an NCTJ journalism course.
          </p>
          <p>
            Previously I briefly studied Mathematics at university, and in my efforts for the TV show University Challenge, I have acquired a great affection for Art, Philosophy and Language. Therefore, what exactly I write about any given week, or choose to research, is not easy to predict.
          </p>
          <p>
            Tags will be used to split posts into genre. You may email Taylor@Tamarisk.uk to request notifications on posts, either all posts or by specific genre. Each tag will receive a separate mailing list; names will be added manually, so make it clear in the contact box which articles you wish to receive.
          </p>
          <p>
            Anyone wishing to contact me regarding any pieces I have written, or project opportunities, is very welcome to either email the above address, or contact me directly. I am always open to working on new things if they are sufficiently interesting.
          </p>
          <p>
            My current academic project I am starting for my 4th year Dissertation is an Environmental Economics study of offshore wind turbine impacts. My previous university projects include a large scale anthropogenic dust study, research into anthropogenic impacts on diatoms, microplastics, and modelling climate impacts on disease carrying mosquito populations.
          </p>
          <p>
            As above, emails are welcome on these topics should you wish for assistance communicating these topics or to be sent my favourite papers on each.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-left lg:border-l lg:border-gray-300 lg:pl-8 dark:lg:border-gray-600">
        <div>
          <p class="px-2 py-3 text-left text-2xl font-bold">About me - The Other Stuff</p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-base leading-8 text-[#032922] dark:text-[#f5e5d5]">
          <p>
            I'm a 24 year old living in Norfolk, UK. My previous career in Esports can be found on an esports wiki site here: <a href="https://liquipedia.net/rocketleague/Jota" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">https://liquipedia.net/rocketleague/Jota</a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Outside of all of the above reading and researching described, I can regularly be found walking by a lake, or woodland. Failing that, I regularly get lured back into revisiting chess after a stint of regular club chess as a child.
          </p>
          <p>
            I also cook extensively but vehemently refuse to turn my website into a food blog. I tried that once with my Instagram account at age 14 and never again.
          </p>
          <div class="pt-6 border-t border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-600">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">People I'd like to talk to</h2>
            <p class="pt-4">
              <strong>To assist the writing of my current projects, I would be grateful to anyone who is, or can put me in touch with, any of the following people:</strong>
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pt-4 text-base leading-8">
              <li>People who fish/traul commercially and are regularly on boats</li>
              <li>Anyone who would consider themselves a genuine expert in JMW Turner, or accessing records and logs from the 19th century</li>
              <li>Professional Sports Statisticians</li>
              <li>Any coaches of rare/niche sports in the UK</li>
              <li>Anyone with a cool scientific discovery or story they'd like me to write about</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="pt-4">
              I can be contacted through <a href="mailto:Taylor@Tamarisk.uk" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Taylor@Tamarisk.uk</a>. If reaching out regarding one of these please put "Research Request" in the heading.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
